modules.description: This module defines configuration data for package installations, including OCaml versions and package lists with associated directives. It provides access to predefined packages for global installation or compilation, along with version-specific and any-version-compatible packages. Use this module to retrieve package configurations and OCaml version details for deployment or build processes.

This module organizes package installation configurations, including OCaml versions and associated package lists with directives. It supports retrieving predefined global or version-specific packages for deployment or build workflows. Key operations include accessing package metadata, resolving version compatibility, and compiling package sets. For example, it can fetch a list of packages compatible with a specific OCaml version or determine dependencies for a given configuration.
